Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the reliability of crowdsourcing studies for psychophysics. This involves the use of comparison-based data and the comparison of results from a lab experiment and an experiment on Amazon Mechanical Turk. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms. Additionally, cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may also be relevant due to the use of triplet questions and the study of crowdsourcing platforms.
